The paper deals with optimization problems related to information theory and channel coding, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of convex optimization techniques and geometric interpretations, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
